Build Instuctions:


Windows: 

* Microsoft Visual Studio 2010 is needed (any non-express edition). (2012 version is unsupported - boost is precomipled for vs2010, no VS plugin for Qt4, no vdproj support)

* Get and install: Visual Studio Add-in 1.1.11 for Qt4 (http://releases.qt-project.org/vsaddin/qt-vs-addin-1.1.11-opensource.exe)

* Get and install: Python 2.7.* (Windows Installer), http://www.python.org/download/

* Qt 4.8.3, compiled with static runtime (but still not-static due to LGPL).
Get http://releases.qt-project.org/qt4/source/qt-everywhere-opensource-src-4.8.4.zip,

Unpack, edit qt-everywhere-opensource-src-4.8.4\mkspecs\win32-msvc2010:
Replace 
QMAKE_CFLAGS_RELEASE    = -O2 -MD
QMAKE_CFLAGS_RELEASE_WITH_DEBUGINFO += -O2 -MD -Zi
QMAKE_CFLAGS_DEBUG      = -Zi -MDd
with
QMAKE_CFLAGS_RELEASE    = -O2 -MT
QMAKE_CFLAGS_RELEASE_WITH_DEBUGINFO += -O2 -MT -Zi
QMAKE_CFLAGS_DEBUG      = -Zi -MTd

Build:
"c:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio 10.0\vc\vcvarsall.bat"
cd qt-everywhere-opensource-src-4.8.4
configure.exe -debug-and-release -platform win32-msvc2010 -no-qt3support -fast
nmake


* Build Release|Win32 and Release|x64 configutations of debugler/src/debugler.sln 

* build Intstaller project of debugler/src/debugler.sln. This will produce installation files in install build/Win32/Relase/whaat?


Further steps for installing Unit Test prerequisities:

* Install python setup tools: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/setuptools/

* Install required modules:

C:\Python27\scripts\easy_install pyopengl

Try running debugler\src\tests\samples\simple.py

On my machine i had this problem: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/10188595/pyopengl-typeerror-nonetype-object-is-not-callable
Resolved by copying missing DLLs as described



